                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 2489/66.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Squiers</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-07-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Squiers reports that the minister for foreign affairs has particularly
                    requested him to ask the department for a categorical reply to the proposal of
                    Panama for the settlement of the <hi rend="italic">Columbia</hi> and <hi
                        rend="italic">Buffalo</hi> cases, as Panama desires to close the matter.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
